article.headline: Jacksonville St. 72, Tennessee Tech 71
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Will Ginn's layup with 11 seconds left gave Jacksonville State a 72-71 victory over Tennessee Tech Thursday night. The Gamecocks (7-8, 5-11 Ohio Valley Conference) were down five with less than two minutes to play, but they came back to score the final five points to beat the Golden Eagles (14-11, 10-6 OVC). On a 3-point attempt from the right corner with 24 seconds to play, Jacksonville State's Nick Smith was fouled by Amadi McKenzie, sending him to the charity stripe with the Gamecocks down, 71-67. Smith knocked down all three attempts to cut the lead to one. Then when Tennessee Tech's Belton Rivers missed the front end of a one-and-one one second later, setting up Ginn's winning shot. Courtney Bradley led the Gamecocks with 20 points and 11 rebounds. Ginn had 13 and Nick Smith pitched in with 12. Amadi McKenzie was the high scorer for the Golden Eagles with 20 points and 14 rebounds. Belton Rivers added 17, and Anthony Fisher chipped in with 16 more. The Gamecocks shot just 37 percent from the floor to the Golden Eagles' 42 percent, but outrebounded the visitors 42-41.
